{"ModDate": "D:20050303104837+08'00'", "CreationDate": "D:20050302154815+08'00'", "Title": "Samut Prakarn Wastewater Management Project Fifth Semiannual Report To The Board Of Directors On Implementation Of The Recommendations Of The Board Inspection Committee As Adopted On 25 March 2002", "Creator": "Acrobat PDFMaker 6.0 for Word", "Producer": "Acrobat Distiller 6.0 (Windows)", "Author": "", "Company": "Licenced User", "SourceModified": "D:20050302074648", "content": " \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n \n\n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n\n \n\nASIAN DEVELOPMENT BANK \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n\nSAMUT PRAKARN WASTEWATER MANAGEMENT PROJECT \n \nFIFTH SEMIANNUAL  \n\nREPORT \n\nTO THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS \n\nON \n \nIMPLEMENTATION OF THE RECOMMENDATIONS \n \nOF THE BOARD INSPECTION COMMITTEE \n \nAS ADOPTED ON 25 MARCH 2002 \n\n \n\nFebruary 2005 \n\n\f \n\n \n\n \n\nABBREVIATIONS \n\n\u2013 \n\u2013 \n\nAsian Development Bank \nPollution Control Department \n\n \n\n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n\nADB \nPCD \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n\f \n\n \n\nI. \n\nINTRODUCTION AND BACKGROUND \n\n \n\n1. \nOn 25 March 2002, the Board of Directors of the Asian Development Bank (ADB) met to \nconsider the recommendations of the Board Inspection Committee pursuant to the inspection of \nthe ADB-funded Samut Prakarn Wastewater Management Project (the Project) in Thailand.1 At \nthat meeting, the Board noted the report of the committee and, after deliberation, approved its \nrecommendations  as  quoted  in  paragraph  1  of  Board  document  IN.251-02  dated  3  October \n2002.2 This is the fifth semiannual report to the Board, covering the period 26 March 2004 to 25 \nSeptember  2004.  Although  the  report  was  scheduled  to  be  submitted  to  the  Board  in  early \nOctober 2004, it was held back in the expectation of further developments on the Project. \n \n \n\nII. \n\nPROJECT STATUS \n\n2. \nAs noted in the fourth semiannual report, as a result of investigations into the Project in \nearly 2003 initiated by the Minister for Natural Resources and Environment in the Government, \nthe  turnkey  contract  was  declared  null  and  void  on  the  basis  that  there  had  been  contractual \nirregularities. The Executing Agency, the Pollution Control Department (PCD), officially advised \nthe turnkey contractor of its decision on 28 February 2003 and ADB on 18 March 2003. Total \ndisbursement under the main turnkey contract has remained static since that time at about B20 \nbillion, out of a total contract value of about B23 billion (87%). PCD announced that it would file \na civil suit against the turnkey contractor,3 in which it intended to sue for all monies paid to date \nunder the contract.  \n \n3. \nPCD  did  proceed  with  the  filing  of  a  suit  in  May  2004,  requesting  repayment  of  all \nmonies paid under the contract to date, based on its claim that the contract was null and void. \nThe  civil  court  rejected  PCD's  claim,  and  recommended  that  it  seek  resolution  of  the  matter \nthrough the contract\u2019s arbitration provisions. No further progress has been made on this matter. \n \n4. \nsuspended. \n \n5. \nindividuals associated with the acquisition of the land for the wastewater treatment plant. \n \n6. \nannounced. Its review of the Project\u2019s social aspects has not yet commenced. \n \n \n\nAs reported in the fourth semiannual report, work on all project-related activities remains \n\nNo further progress has been made in respect of the fraud charges laid against several \n\nPCD\u2019s review of the Project\u2019s technical aspects is under way, but no findings have been \n\n                                                 \n1   ADB.  1995.  Report  and  Recommendation  of  the  President  to  the  Board  of  Directors  on  a  Proposed  Loan  to  the \nKingdom  of  Thailand  for  the  Samut  Prakarn  Wastewater  Management  Project.  Manila  (Loan  1410-THA);  ADB. \n1998. Report and Recommendation of the President to the Board of Directors on a Proposed Supplementary Loan \nto the Kingdom of Thailand for the Samut Prakarn Wastewater Management Project. Manila (Loan 1646-THA). \n2   ADB. 2002. Samut Prakarn Wastewater Management Project First Semiannual Report to the Board of Directors on \n\nImplementation of the Recommendations of the Board Inspection Committee. Manila. \n\n3   The  turnkey  contractor  comprises  a  consortium  of  companies:  Gateway  Development  Co.  Ltd.,  Krung  Thon \nEngineering Co. Ltd., Prayoonvisava Engineering Co. Ltd., See Sang Karn Yotah (1979) Co. Ltd., and Vichitbhan \nConstruction Co. Ltd. \n\n\f2 \n\n \n\nIII. \n\nCOMPENSATION PLAN, MONITORING SYSTEMS, COMMUNITY \nINVOLVEMENT, AND ODOR AND EFFLUENT MANAGEMENT \n\n7. \nSince the submission of the fourth semiannual report, no further action or progress has \nbeen made on (i) implementation of the resettlement plan, (ii) implementation of the monitoring \nsystems, (iii) community involvement, or (iv) any measures taken that are associated with odor \nand effluent (if any). \n \n\nIV. \n\nCONCLUSION  \n\n8. \nAfter  almost  2  years  of  investigations,  and  following  loan  closure,  the  Project  remains \nincomplete and all project-related activities remain suspended. No further action or progress has \ntaken place with respect to the compensation plan, monitoring activities, community involvement \ninitiatives,  or  odor  and  effluent  management.  No  further  action  will  be  taken  with  respect  to \nthese issues until the contractual dispute between PCD and the turnkey contractor is resolved.  \n \n \n \n\n\f", "author_pages": [" \n", " \n", " \n", "ABBREVIATIONS \n", "\u2013 \n\u2013 \n", "Asian Development Bank \nPollution Control Department \n", " \n", " \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n", "ADB \nPCD \n", " \n", " \n", " \n", " \n", " \n", " \n", "I. \n", "INTRODUCTION AND BACKGROUND \n", " \n", "1. \nOn 25 March 2002, the Board of Directors of the Asian Development Bank (AD